Louis Trichardt will play host to the first round of the Limpopo XCO mountain-bike league on 21 January at Komatiland Forestry just outside of town. This event sanctioned by Cycling South Africa (CSA) is sponsored by PSG Insure. Entry for the Nippers and Sprogs category is R100 and R200 for all other categories. A day licence from non-CSA members will cost R50. In addition to the normal categories,  a new 30+ age category on a short track, as well as more laps for E-bikes, will be available. For online entries, go to rorevents.co.za, and for more information, phone Stanley at 082 493 3897 or Kombo at 071 119 5635.